ACTRESS Masasa Mbangeni, who is best known for her role as Thembeka Shezi on e.tv’s Scandal!, has shared that her dad died with a broken heart. “My father was unemployed after he had been retrenched and it broke his heart. He tried every day to secure work but there was none. He died of a broken heart. Don’t date unemployed people if your capacity for compassion is at negative none,” she said. “Nisihleba kwiTshomi who treat us badly because of your utterances. It’s not right. You have a right to your values and ideals. Pursue them with the same vigour used to abuse unemployed partners.” Her reason for opening up about her dad’s passing comes after she shared her theory around people who are employed and choose to date unemployed people. ALSO READ | SINGLE AND MINGE COUPLE WOES! She said people do this because they are too scared to date people of their calibre or higher because they know in that space, they would be treated like how they treat unemployed people and they simply wouldn’t cope with the other belittling them. Masasa’s discussion opened a can of worms and people joined in with many saying people forget that there are no guarantees in life. “The very same unemployed person you’re looking down on and mistreating and gossiping about might rise and find work. And it happens that you also lose your job for some reason, then what?” said Kgomotso Tlhapane. Nonny wrote: “So many men are committing suicide for this very reason. Unemployment in this country is the real pandemic.” Melvin said he is heartbroken because he was once dumped because he did not have money for a birthday present. My father was unemployed after he had been retrenched and it broke his heart. He tried every day to secure work but there was none. He died of a broken heart. Don’t date unemployed people if your capacity for compassion is at negative none . Nisihleba kwiTshomi 